---
layout: base.njk
title: Rebekah Monson
description: Media entrepreneur, community builder, and civic technologist helping journalism and communities thrive.
---

{# ===== HERO ===== #}
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container hero-inner">
    <p class="hero-greeting">Hey, I'm Rebekah <span class="emoji-hover" data-animation="wave">&#x1F44B;</span></p>
    <h1 class="hero-headline">
      I build things that make <span class="accent">communities stronger.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      Media entrepreneur, civic technologist, and community builder in Miami.
      I help organizations and newsrooms connect with the people they serve.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn--primary">Let's work together</a>
      <a href="#about" class="btn btn--outline">Learn more</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ===== ABOUT ===== #}
<section class="section" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <img src="/img/headshot.jpg" alt="Rebekah Monson" class="about-photo" loading="lazy">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          I'm a co-founder, operator, and strategist who has spent a career at the intersection of
          journalism, technology, and civic life <span class="emoji-hover" data-animation="pop">&#x2728;</span>
        </p>
        <p>
          As co-founder and COO of <a href="https://tryletterhead.com">Letterhead</a>, I build software
          that helps publishers create, manage, and monetize community-driven newsletters. Before that,
          I co-founded <a href="https://whereby.us">WhereBy.Us</a>, whose local newsletter brands
          &mdash; The New Tropic, The Evergrey, Bridgeliner, Pulptown, and The Incline &mdash; engaged
          more than a million curious locals each year across five cities.
        </p>
        <p>
          I also co-founded <a href="https://codeforsouth.org/">Code for Miami</a>, the city's first
          civic hacking organization, and <a href="https://commissioner.us">Commissioner</a>, a local
          art membership program. I serve on boards including
          <a href="https://www.lionpublishers.com/">LION Publishers</a> and the
          <a href="https://miamifoundation.org/">Miami Foundation</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          I hold an MFA in Interactive Media from the University of Miami and a BA in Journalism
          and Graphic Design from LSU. When I'm not building things, you'll find me
          exploring Miami with entirely too many opinions about coffee.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

